"v.限制 【英】 v. 限制 (to restrict; restrain; limit) 【记】 circum(绕圈)+scribe (画)→画一个圈子→ 限制 【同】 同根词：describe(描 述); prescribe(开处方, 规定) 【例】 Rules set down by her parents circumscribed her activities. v. 限制; 约束 = restrict = restrain = limit 【例】Their life was extremely circumscribed 他们的生活范围太局限了. 【记】circum圈, scribe画－画一个圈－限制(想想唐僧被孙悟空划一个圈, 限制他的自由) 【参】describe(v 描述); prescribe(v 开处方, 规定) 【反】circumscribed(限制的)－unlimited(无限的) 【记】circum 周围 + scribe 写→在.周围画线，限制 【相关】ascribe 归功于、归咎于某人, circumscribe 在.周围画线, 限制 ，conscribe 征召，强召入伍，describe描写 记述，inscribe写，刻，记下，prescribe 指示，规定，开处方，proscribe 禁止，scribble乱写，subscribe 赞成，签署，superscribe 将(姓名和住址)写在信封,包裹上,transcribe 转录 circumscribe (v.)  late 14c., from Latin circumscribere ""to make a circle around, encircle, draw a line around; limit, restrain, confine, set the boundaries of,"" from circum- ""around"" (see circum-) + scribere ""write"" (see script (n.)). Related: Circumscribed; circumscribing."
